@startuml Image Generation Sequence
' Image Generation Flow
' Shows the image generation process with character consistency

actor User
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "FastAPI Backend" as API
participant "Director Agent" as Director
participant "Image Agent" as ImageAgent
participant "Stable Diffusion" as SD
participant "IP-Adapter" as IPAdapter
participant "File System" as FS

User -> FE: Enable image generation
FE -> API: POST /api/generate (with images: true)
API -> Director: Start pipeline with image flag

Director -> ImageAgent: Generate scene illustrations
ImageAgent -> ImageAgent: Process scene descriptions
ImageAgent -> ImageAgent: Create image prompts

loop For each scene
    ImageAgent -> SD: Generate initial image
    SD -> ImageAgent: Base scene image
    
    alt Character consistency enabled
        ImageAgent -> IPAdapter: Apply character consistency
        IPAdapter -> IPAdapter: Maintain character appearance
        IPAdapter -> ImageAgent: Consistent character image
    end
    
    ImageAgent -> ImageAgent: Apply style transfer
    ImageAgent -> ImageAgent: Upscale and enhance
    ImageAgent -> FS: Save image file
    FS -> ImageAgent: File path confirmation
end

ImageAgent -> Director: All images generated
Director -> API: Story with image URLs
API -> FE: Story data with image paths
FE -> User: Display story with illustrations

note right of ImageAgent
  **Image Generation Process:**
  1. Process scene descriptions
  2. Generate base images with SD
  3. Apply character consistency
  4. Style transfer and upscaling
  5. Save to file system
end note

@enduml
